New CLIs:
  sw(config)# [no] video <slot> udp <dest_udp> <qam_int> pass-through
  sw(config)# [no] video <slot> multicast source-address <src_ip>
                         dest-address <dest_ip> <qam_int> pass-through

New test CLIs:
  sw# test video <slot> qam <qam_id>
  sw# test video <slot> port udp <dest_udp>
  sw# test video <slot> port multicast <src_ip> <dest_ip>


Changes in major data structures:
  vn_qam:
    Add boolean passthru_flag;

  udp_port_map:
    Use mask PORT_PASSTHRU (0x10) to flags


New defines:
  #define PASSTHRU_PROG_NUM    0


Notes:
  - Passthru session can be either UDP or MCAST, and can be either SPTS or MPTS.
  - For passthru port map, the flag will have PORT_PASSTHRU set,
    the program number will be PASSTHRU_PROG_NUM.
  - For QAM used for passthru, the passthru_flag flag is set in vn_qam.
    The out_prog_list will contain all the out_prog, one for each program.


New subroutines:
  cc_map_passthru()
    Add SPTS/MPTS passthru program for each qam in the port_map's qam_prog_list.

  cc_unmap_passthru()
    Delete SPTS/MPTS passthru program for each qam in the port_map's
    qam_prog_list.

  cc_add_mpts_program()
    Create outprog, one for each program in MPTS, and link them to
    inprog and qam.  Send output_config message and update PAT in LC.

  cc_delete_mpts_program()
    Remove all outprog in qam's out_prog_list, unlink them to the inprog.
    Destroy out_prog_list.  Update PAT in LC.

  cc_provision_passthru()
    Send output_config message to LC, with outputprogram number set to
    PASSTHRU_PROG_NUM.
